One of the main issues I get tons of DM’s about is hiring drivers!🚛

First of all you have to set the criteria for your company and make your applicants adhere to that, rather than being desperate for any ole driver.📉📈

From the onset, if a person who wants a job with your company  can’t even follow the first round of  instructions, STOP WASTING YOUR TIME with them!🚫

Automatically disqualify them!🙅🏾‍♀️

You don’t have the time to teach them how to properly apply for the position and it’s a RED FLAG!!🚫

Would you be comfortable with your surgeon performing surgery on you without his/her proper credentials???🩺🩻

Same scenario.💎

Following instructions is one way to vett your driver before even hiring them. ☠️

Chances are if they can’t follow a simple application process, they won’t be a great fit for your company anyways.🤷🏽‍♀️

Your giving someone an opportunity to make money with your company. It’s a win win and beneficial for both parties. ✅✅

If they can’t adhere to the procedure, find someone else who can and will!☝🏾
